                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BONUS-MALUS</span> :-A bonus-malus system is a No-claim Bonus (or No-claim Discount) system in which the premium level reached after a policyholder has made claims may be higher than that corresponding to the point of entry. The term is used throughout Continental Europe and elsewhere.
                        </li>
                        
                        <!-- BANCASSURANCE -->
                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BANCASSURANCE</span> :-Involvement of banks in the traditional insurance market.
                        </li>
                        
                        <!-- BILL OF LADING -->
                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BILL OF LADING</span> :- Document detailing the transfer of goods from a (foreign) supplier to a buyer. It may be used as a document of title.
                        </li>
                        
                        <!-- BLANKET INSURANCE -->
                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BLANKET INSURANCE</span> :- A policy designed to provide coverage under a single limit for two or more items (e.g. building and/or contents), two or more locations, or a combination of items and/or locations.
                        </li>
                        
                        <!-- BREAK BULK -->
                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BREAK BULK</span> :- Carriage of goods other than by container.
                        </li>
                        
                        <!-- BROKER -->
                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BROKER</span> :- A marketing specialist who represents buyers of insurance and who deals with companies in arranging for the coverage required by the customer.
                        </li>
                        
                        <!-- BURGLARY -->
                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BURGLARY</span> :- Breaking and entering into another person's property with felonious intent.
                        </li>
                        
                        <!-- BUSINESS INTERRUPTION INSURANCE -->
                        <li class="dictionary-item">
                            <span>BUSINESS INTERRUPTION INSURANCE</span> :- Protection for a business owner against losses resulting from a temporary shutdown because of fire or other insured peril. The insurance provides reimbursement for lost net profits and necessary continuing expenses.
                        </li>
                        
                    </ul>
